@nielsdg I'm a little confused..
`Predicate` has two properties - `flags` and `nflags`.

While matching an object and a predicate, the same operations are performed for both the properties :confused: 

```
if (this.flags != Flags.NONE && (obj_flags in this.flags))
    return false;
if (this.nflags != Flags.NONE && (obj_flags in this.nflags))
    return false;
```

At the moment, I've made the assumption that `Predicate.flags` are the required flags for an object to be included

@khaledh, this issue is reproducible with many fonts, so this is not a font issue.

I also tried different versions of `libfreetype` which doesn't seem to cause any difference, so looks like it is not freetype issue either.

If you think this is not a Pango issue, maybe you could suggest what else can cause this problem? Any way I can debug where this space comes from?
